public interface Tuple6<A,B,C,D,E,F> extends Tuple
A tuple that always contains six elements. More formally: T3 = (t0, t1, t2, t3, t4, t5) or |T6| = 6. The Tuple6 interface extends Tuple and provides all his behaviour. The Tuple6 interface additionally provides one method for the accessing a tuple elements using getters getT0, getT1, getT2, getT3, getT4 and getT5.
